<p>A <code>treeitem</code> should be placed inside a <span class="script">XULElem("treechildren")</span> element and should contain <span class="script">XULElem("treerow")</span> elements. The <code>treeitem</code> can be clicked by the user to select the row of the tree. The <code>treeitem</code> contains a single row and all of what appear to the user as that row's descendants.</p>
<p>In a template condition, you should use a <code>treeitem</code> instead of a <span class="script">XULElem("content")</span> element when the <code>dont-build-content</code> flag is specified. Set the <span class="script">XULAttr("uri")</span> attribute to the variable name to bind to a content node during matching.</p>
<p>More information is available in the <a title="en/XUL_Tutorial/Trees" href="/en/XUL_Tutorial/Trees">XUL tutorial</a>.</p>
<dl> <dt>Attributes</dt> <dd><span class="script">PrefAnch("a-", "container")</span>, <span class="script">PrefAnch("a-", "empty")</span>, <span class="script">PrefAnch("a-", "treeitem.label", "label")</span>, <span class="script">PrefAnch("a-", "open")</span>, <span class="script">PrefAnch("a-", "uri")</span></dd>
</dl>
